        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 8:21PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 821 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Marvell, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cody, Hughes, Clack, Lake Cormorant, Cottonwood Corner, Haleside,
Commerce, Soudan, Round Pond, Vineyard, Beck, Simsboro, Democrat,
Brickeys, Ball Point, Whitehall, Tongin, Raggio, Poplar Grove, and
Mississippi River State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for eastern
Arkansas...and northwestern Mississippi.</instruction>
